# Following tutorial from
# http://www.idryman.org/blog/2016/03/10/autoconf-tutorial-1/

# The original files in the directory (along with this note) are:
configure.ac hello.c makefile.am

# This command creates the configure script:
autoreconf --verbose --install --force

# Then one can execute the configure script to create the Makefile:
./configure

# Then one can do
make

# Which produces the executable
hello.x
